relation: They are awesome and will walk you to your class if you have any night classes.
The church on campus often does events and the science club takes awesome trips.
Don't spend your financial aid check save every penny you can in case you need it. Also watch how many hours you take and DO NOT reach your maximum hours.
Focus on studies but have a little fun on the weekend.
They have awesome food. You will love the diner. Their pudding cups rock especially the chocolate.
I don't live on campus but I'm sure its great. I don't here of any complaints, Not sure how you would go about living on the campus.

If you do anatomy make sure to take Dr. Fleming not Mrs. Rich. Also take biology and chemistry before taking this. Also take a bunch of not so hard classes so you can focus on this. If you do nursing and you want to audit anatomy dont because they count your first class so make sure that you do great and dont slack off. Research teachers on rate my professor.com
Make sure to ask around on the best teachers and make sure to talk to your adviser about your future classes and what your future is for graduating. Set goals and work hard.
This is a good school. Work hard. You can do anything you put your mind too,
